President Trump delivered remarks at the Hyatt Regency Da Nang Resort and Spa in Vietnam to honor veterans of the Vietnam War. He expressed his gratitude for their service and sacrifice, and praised their bravery and patriotism. He also highlighted his administration's commitment to rebuilding the military and improving the Veterans Administration. Trump signed a proclamation to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Vietnam War. He invited several veterans to speak, who expressed their admiration and support for the President. The event concluded with the signing of the proclamation.